WEBVTT

00:13.600 --> 00:19.760
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen. It's really a pleasure and an honor to be here and give

00:19.760 --> 00:28.880
you a brief description of some of Israeli high-tech aspects. I'll try to do it briefly

00:28.880 --> 00:35.560
because I guess that we are kind of slipping a little bit on the timetable and later on probably if

00:35.560 --> 00:41.080
you would like to ask more specific questions we'll be in the round table and I'll be more than

00:41.080 --> 00:47.060
happy to answer on any specific questions. So I'm going to concentrate mostly on the electronics

00:47.060 --> 00:56.540
and the software industries of Israel and just briefly describe to you what we do. In general

00:56.540 --> 01:03.400
absolute terms obviously our electronic industry is not so big probably as the Italian one but

01:03.400 --> 01:11.820
it still represents Israel being a small country more than 26 percent you will see of the total

01:11.820 --> 01:19.580
export and also quite substantial part of our gross national product. In general the revenue

01:19.580 --> 01:26.200
is growing at the rate of about 13 to 15 percent a year, the export at about 15 percent a year and

01:26.200 --> 01:33.000
it is typical as you may know to the high-tech industries usually they grow twice or three

01:33.000 --> 01:39.300
times as much as fast as the gross national product and that is in any country. I mean if the GDP or

01:39.300 --> 01:44.280
GNP grows at about six percent you'll find that the high-tech industry grows at about 15 percent

01:44.280 --> 01:49.500
and that's the reason for a shortage of manpower that has just been described by the Prime

01:49.500 --> 01:55.200
Minister. We are kind of running the world is running fast we are in the information society

01:55.200 --> 02:01.500
and obviously the educational system did not gear itself up to the fast development which

02:01.500 --> 02:07.080
are happening at the high-tech industry and we have this same symptom. Presently we have about

02:07.080 --> 02:14.620
40,000 employees within the output per employee which comes to about the 1996 figures as already

02:14.620 --> 02:25.700
at the range of about $170,000 per employee in this specific industry. As you may see the major

02:25.700 --> 02:32.940
development of the industry is toward the export I mean you are pretty constant on the local volume

02:32.940 --> 02:40.080
the reason being is that at the past the bigger consumer of our local production was the military

02:40.080 --> 02:46.400
but defense budgets are being cut all over the world and also in Israel and we are diverting more

02:46.400 --> 02:53.660
and more into the commercial and civilian markets and we are taking obviously technologies that

02:53.660 --> 03:00.600
have been derived from the military field into the civilian electronics which was again described

03:00.600 --> 03:09.160
by the Prime Minister as one of the sources to our high growth in that sector. You can see that the

03:09.160 --> 03:16.140
sectors in the export market of the electronic business would be between components industrial

03:16.140 --> 03:23.380
medical military and the fastest growing one is the communication which grows really at about 30% a

03:23.380 --> 03:29.640
year that is twice as fast as the total electronic sector is in the communication and I assume that

03:29.640 --> 03:36.880
in Italy probably it might be the same. In terms of the segment that I would say that the high

03:36.880 --> 03:45.000
growth represent out of the total exports you see it's about 26% but it's going very up and if

03:45.000 --> 03:51.860
you ask my estimate in about 10 years from now it might constitute more than 50 or even 60% of

03:51.860 --> 03:57.600
our total export because this is again as I said is the fastest growing field that we have today

03:58.520 --> 04:06.720
and is based mostly on know-how and not on raw materials. You can also see very clearly that

04:06.720 --> 04:11.780
we are going down in the military side but we are going up in the civilian side so there is

04:11.780 --> 04:19.220
definite shift from the military export and military electronics into civilian electronics.

04:20.600 --> 04:27.580
Just a few facts about the competitiveness in the sector. You can see let's say if you are

04:27.580 --> 04:33.320
talking hourly wages in the electronic sector and we are comparing let's say USA Italy USA

04:33.320 --> 04:41.720
Canada you can see where Israel stands at about $12 per hour fully loaded that would be the

04:41.720 --> 04:46.460
cost for production in the high-tech sector in Israel obviously in other sectors it is lower

04:46.460 --> 04:53.520
but you can see that if you go to Germany or Holland and these places it's a much higher and

04:53.520 --> 05:00.940
again I'm talking about production worker so there is a merit there is a merit for a production in

05:00.940 --> 05:07.540
Israel even though we have a quite high of GNP per capita as was mentioned of about $17,000 per

05:10.240 --> 05:18.580
capita. In general the high-tech output represent as I said about 50% of the industrial production

05:18.580 --> 05:25.500
at all, 65% of Israel export in the high-tech field. We have the higher per capita number of

05:25.500 --> 05:30.480
science graduates worldwide I'll show it in a minute. The research and development spending

05:30.480 --> 05:36.500
of about 3% of the GDP is the highest in the world I'll show it again in comparison and we believe

05:36.500 --> 05:41.280
that we have the highest concentration of startups outside the Silicon Valley and you take this the

05:41.940 --> 05:47.560
area of Israel is about the area of California and registered and unregistered startup you come to

05:47.560 --> 05:51.760
about 3,000 startups and we don't know of any other place in the world where you have this kind

05:51.760 --> 06:00.880
of a concentration of startup dealing with high-tech. In terms of comparison in research and

06:00.880 --> 06:07.040
development you can see on the graph percentage wise I mean Israel is at the top of the list

06:07.040 --> 06:12.560
obviously if you're talking in absolute values that's a different story because after all we

06:12.560 --> 06:19.200
don't have a trillion dollar economy but only something like 70-80 billion dollars but

06:19.200 --> 06:23.880
percentage wise you can see the effort that we are doing in terms of promoting the research

06:23.880 --> 06:29.300
and development and our chief scientist Dr. Honor Burry is going to refer to it in the next lecture.

06:31.260 --> 06:37.300
In terms of distribution of profession again it was mentioned by the Prime Minister you can see

06:37.300 --> 06:42.840
that due to the concentration on the high-tech as well as the absorption of the immigration from

06:42.840 --> 06:52.720
the Soviet Union in terms of technical profession a concentration and proportion to capita you see

06:52.720 --> 06:59.220
that Israel stands again ahead of the USA, Japan, Korea or Germany in terms of technical professions

06:59.220 --> 07:07.320
per the population. In terms of holder of science and engineering post-garage degrees this is the

07:07.320 --> 07:15.840
1995 figure but it's not very different from the 1996 you see again that in science and

07:15.840 --> 07:23.080
engineering in post-graduates per 10,000 in working population we have about close to four

07:23.080 --> 07:30.660
and a half percent which is very very high therefore in half per 10,000 excuse me. What are the areas

07:30.660 --> 07:37.620
in which you are concentrating? They are quite numerous. All of them really kind of have been

07:37.620 --> 07:43.220
identified as future areas and they would be in the information technology, environmental technologies,

07:43.680 --> 07:48.980
electronics and electro-optics, optics and lasers, multimedia, medical technology, telecommunication,

07:49.420 --> 07:54.740
data communication, sensing and biotechnology. These would be the main areas in which we are

07:56.240 --> 08:03.640
just to give you an idea if we go and innovation that we have in our startups some of them are

08:03.640 --> 08:08.080
worldwide innovations that is we were the first one to introduce them into the world market and

08:08.380 --> 08:15.580
they would be on multiplexing system based on SDHs, Gronius digital hierarchy standards, voice and

08:15.580 --> 08:20.960
handwritten recognition, wireless local area networks, voice and video compression and internet

08:20.960 --> 08:26.400
communication for video, voice, data, fax. We were the first one to introduce them. Companies like

08:26.400 --> 08:32.220
Wacaltech and so on. Firewall security for internet. Companies like checkpoint. They came first into

08:32.220 --> 08:37.340
the market identifying really huge potential of the internet that we have today. Intelligent

08:37.340 --> 08:44.140
cabling, computer-based high-speed color printing and many other really state-of-the-art fields in

08:44.140 --> 08:50.220
which we are involved in our operation. Just to show you since the information technology and

08:50.220 --> 08:57.580
internet is a very hot issue today, we are obviously developing a lot of things for the era of

08:57.580 --> 09:03.080
electronic commerce over the internet which is going really to revolutionize all the way in which

09:03.080 --> 09:10.400
we do business banking, schooling, shopping and so on. So we are going obviously into the smart card

09:10.400 --> 09:14.320
issue, electronic commerce, voice and video communication on the internet, firewall safe,

09:14.460 --> 09:19.940
remote access, wireless internet access to bypass the telephone systems that we have, network

09:19.940 --> 09:26.000
management, imaging and pattern recognition, signature recognition, fault detection, encryption

09:26.000 --> 09:31.220
and many other things. Some of them are derived obviously from our military technologies but all

09:31.220 --> 09:38.480
are being applied today very intensively into the fast-rapiding field of the internet. If we are

09:38.480 --> 09:43.020
talking about telecommunication which is again the fast-growing sector in our electronic high

09:43.020 --> 09:49.920
speed network, we are dealing with satellite terminals, ISDN terminals, ATM and LAN switches or SDH which

09:49.920 --> 09:56.340
are really the new switching technologies of the future to enable switching of data from all kind,

09:56.940 --> 10:02.800
two-way radios, cellular radios, video encryption and compression, HDSL and ADSL to enable

10:02.800 --> 10:08.400
transmission of high-speed data on corporate telephone lines, CATV communication because we

10:08.400 --> 10:13.180
are going to open now the cable television also for telephone, multimedia and interactive

10:13.180 --> 10:19.560
application, not just broadcasting on a cable TV and various telephone exchanges, multiplexer,

10:19.600 --> 10:26.800
router, statistical modems. They are all to be found in many of these companies. Israel is also very

10:26.800 --> 10:35.240
known for the electro-optics and lasers. Again, this is a military-deriven technologies and we

10:35.240 --> 10:41.580
have more than 100 companies and 30 technology incubators in the field. Some of them you might

10:41.580 --> 10:47.440
have heard about like Indigo, Cytex, Orbotech, L.O., Planoptics and the specialization would be in

10:47.440 --> 10:54.280
testing, measurement, inspection, digital printing, military, obviously lasers, imaging, fall detection,

10:54.620 --> 11:01.640
manufacturing, medical systems, medical application like surgery, microsurgery, they all fall into

11:01.640 --> 11:11.080
that one. Israel is also very known as a kind of world center for software development. Actually among

11:11.080 --> 11:18.800
very famous centers in Japan, India, Brazil, U.S. and Israel are considered to be a club of very

11:18.800 --> 11:30.720
high advanced software development capabilities and we have more than 200 software houses that are

11:30.720 --> 11:35.940
traded on the NASDAQ. By the way, out of the high-tech companies, Israel is the second country after Canada,

11:36.080 --> 11:44.180
today maybe the first one, which has got companies traded at the NASDAQ, the New York Stock Exchange.

11:45.360 --> 11:50.780
They have been able to raise more than $3 billion in that stock exchange and the value of the companies

11:50.780 --> 11:56.080
today there is over $30 billion and it's quite substantial in comparison to any other country

11:56.080 --> 11:59.580
which is investing in the U.S. or trying to raise money for high-tech products.

